The paper discusses privacy models in the context of databases, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. The paper also discusses statistical inference and differential privacy, which are topics commonly studied in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper addresses issues related to utility and vulnerability to auxiliary information, which are topics that fall under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a solution to address the drawbacks of previous approaches, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category.
